  "texts": [
    "For feature abstraction, AlexNet employs a large number of convolutional kernels.",
    "Net makes advantage of deeper and larger networks to improve the network's feature learning skills.",
    "In comparison to VGGNet and AlexNet, GoogleNet can extract feature maps of many perceptual domains, improving the width and depth of the network while lowering the network parameters.",
    "ResNet uses the residual structure to tackle the network degradation problem when the model is deeper.",
    "DenseNet employs a densely linked topology that allows features to be reused and the number of network parameters to be reduced."
